<h1 class="title">sh match multiple conditions in one case</h1>
<p>
Using ;;&amp; in place of ;; causes the shell to test the next pattern list in
the statement, if any, and execute any associated list on a successful
match.
</p>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-sh" id="org86dac30">function cs() {
  case $1 in
    1)
      echo "Mon";;
    2|3|4|5)
      echo "Tue|Wed|Thu|Fri";;&amp;
    5|6|7)
      echo "Fri|Sat|Sun";;
    # 3)
      # echo "Wed";;
    # 2|3)
      # echo "Wed";;
    *)
      echo "Nothing matched";;
  esac
  echo
}
cs 1
cs 3
cs 5
</pre>
